### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@token = YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
@classId = YOUR_CLASS_ID_HERE
@studentId = YOUR_STUDENT_ID_HERE
@gradeId = YOUR_GRADE_ID_HERE

### ============================================
### GRADES MODULE - API TESTING
### ============================================

### 1. Add a new grade to a class
POST {{baseUrl}}/grades/{{classId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "student": "{{studentId}}",
  "subject": "Mathematics",
  "score": 85,
  "term": "Q1 2024"
}

### 2. Add another grade with different subject
POST {{baseUrl}}/grades/{{classId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "student": "{{studentId}}",
  "subject": "Science",
  "score": 92,
  "term": "Q1 2024"
}

### 3. Get all grades for a student
GET {{baseUrl}}/grades/student/{{studentId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 4. Get all grades for a class
GET {{baseUrl}}/grades/class/{{classId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5. Get a specific grade by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/grades/{{gradeId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6. Update a grade
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/grades/{{gradeId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "score": 95,
  "term": "Q2 2024"
}

### 7. Update only the score
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/grades/{{gradeId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "score": 88
}

### 8. Delete a grade (Admin only)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/grades/{{gradeId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ============================================
### ERROR SCENARIOS
### ============================================

### 9. Try to add grade with invalid score (> 100)
POST {{baseUrl}}/grades/{{classId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "student": "{{studentId}}",
  "subject": "Mathematics",
  "score": 150,
  "term": "Q1 2024"
}

### 10. Try to add grade with invalid score (< 0)
POST {{baseUrl}}/grades/{{classId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "student": "{{studentId}}",
  "subject": "Mathematics",
  "score": -10,
  "term": "Q1 2024"
}

### 11. Try to add grade without required fields
POST {{baseUrl}}/grades/{{classId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject": "Mathematics"
}

### 12. Try to get grades without authentication
GET {{baseUrl}}/grades/student/{{studentId}}

